did.unittitle: Preliminary Guide to the Washington State University College of Engineering Research Division Correspondence, Minutes, Reports, and Speeches
did.abstract: Research files from the WSU Research Division the from 1940s to 1970. Includes research study files, investigative research, specimen preparation documents, and Model Experiments.

bioghist.p: The Research Division of the College of Engineering was originally the Division of Industrial Research (DIR), established at Washington State University in 1946. The DIR conducted studies and research leading toward the economical use of material resources in the Northwest and the broad, well-balanced development of the state. The DIR was reorganized in 1966 under the College of Engineering. Dr. E. W. Greenfield was the director of the Research Division from 1966 until 1972 when Dr. George Marra took over as head, until his retirement in 1980.

scopecontent.p: Research files from the WSU Research Division from the 1940s-1970. Includes Research study files, Investigative research, specimen preparation documents, Model Experiments, miscellaneous files, and budget files. A preliminary item by item guide exists to boxes 1-45.

arrangement.p: This is an unprocessed collection. Any arrangement reflects either a pre-existing order from the records' creators or previous custodians, or preliminary sorting performed by staff.
Items remain in their original order. Some folders are labeled and dated while others contain no date. A preliminary item by item list exists and is included in this guide.

accessrestrict.p: This collection is open and available for research use.

prefercite.p: Preliminary Guide to the Washington State University College of Engineering Research Division Correspondence, Minutes, Reports, and Speeches, circa 1940s-1970 (UA1983-04)
Manuscripts, Archives, and Special Collections, Washington State University Libraries, Pullman, WA.

acqinfo.p: This material was transferred to WSU Libraries' MASC by Nick Staba and Steve Garl of the College of Engineering on March 15, 1983 and retained as UA1983-04.

controlaccess.p: This collection is indexed under the following headings in the online catalog. Researchers desiring materials about related topics, persons, or places should search the catalog using these headings.
